{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1166,"text":"For much of the past century,"},{"time":2882,"text":"architecture was under the spell\nof a famous doctrine."},{"time":6396,"text":"\"Form follows function\" had become\nmodernity's ambitious manifesto"},{"time":10015,"text":"and detrimental straitjacket,"},{"time":12292,"text":"as it liberated architecture\nfrom the decorative,"},{"time":15285,"text":"but condemned it to utilitarian rigor\nand restrained purpose."},{"time":20418,"text":"Of course, architecture is about function,"},{"time":23148,"text":"but I want to remember a rewriting\nof this phrase by Bernard Tschumi,"},{"time":26839,"text":"and I want to propose\na completely different quality."},{"time":31140,"text":"If form follows fiction,"},{"time":33556,"text":"we could think of architecture\nand buildings as a space of stories --"},{"time":37763,"text":"stories of the people that live there,"},{"time":40267,"text":"of the people that work\nin these buildings."},{"time":43088,"text":"And we could start to imagine\nthe experiences our buildings create."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47965,"text":"In this sense, I'm interested in fiction"},{"time":50592,"text":"not as the implausible but as the real,"},{"time":54194,"text":"as the reality of what architecture means"},{"time":56216,"text":"for the people that live\nin it and with it."},{"time":59666,"text":"Our buildings are prototypes,\nideas for how the space of living"},{"time":63289,"text":"or how the space of working\ncould be different,"},{"time":66728,"text":"and what a space of culture\nor a space of media could look like today."},{"time":71246,"text":"Our buildings are real;\nthey're being built."},{"time":73350,"text":"They're an explicit engagement\nin physical reality"},{"time":76233,"text":"and conceptual possibility."},{"time":80013,"text":"I think of our architecture\nas organizational structures."},{"time":84276,"text":"At their core is indeed\nstructural thinking, like a system:"},{"time":87928,"text":"How can we arrange things\nin both a functional"},{"time":91103,"text":"and experiential way?"},{"time":94188,"text":"How can we create structures\nthat generate a series"},{"time":96880,"text":"of relationships and narratives?"},{"time":99672,"text":"And how can fictive stories"},{"time":101287,"text":"of the inhabitants and users\nof our buildings"},{"time":104125,"text":"script the architecture,"},{"time":106101,"text":"while the architecture scripts\nthose stories at the same time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":110428,"text":"And here comes the second term into play,"},{"time":112437,"text":"what I call \"narrative hybrids\" --"},{"time":114699,"text":"structures of multiple\nsimultaneous stories"},{"time":117468,"text":"that unfold throughout\nthe buildings we create."},{"time":120706,"text":"So we could think of architecture\nas complex systems of relationships,"},{"time":125590,"text":"both in a programmatic and functional way"},{"time":128898,"text":"and in an experiential\nand emotive or social way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135187,"text":"This is the headquarters\nfor China's national broadcaster,"},{"time":137958,"text":"which I designed together\nwith Rem Koolhaas at OMA."},{"time":141882,"text":"When I first arrived in Beijing in 2002,\nthe city planners showed us this image:"},{"time":146045,"text":"a forest of several hundred skyscrapers"},{"time":148236,"text":"to emerge in the central\nbusiness district,"},{"time":150331,"text":"except at that time,\nonly a handful of them existed."},{"time":153389,"text":"So we had to design in a context\nthat we knew almost nothing about,"},{"time":156676,"text":"except one thing:\nit would all be about verticality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160366,"text":"Of course, the skyscraper is vertical --\nit's a profoundly hierarchical structure,"},{"time":165169,"text":"the top always the best,\nthe bottom the worst,"},{"time":167609,"text":"and the taller you are,\nthe better, so it seems."},{"time":171661,"text":"And we wanted to ask ourselves,"},{"time":173194,"text":"could a building be about\na completely different quality?"},{"time":176011,"text":"Could it undo this hierarchy,\nand could it be about a system"},{"time":179988,"text":"that is more about collaboration,\nrather than isolation?"},{"time":183236,"text":"So we took this needle\nand bent it back into itself,"},{"time":186314,"text":"into a loop of interconnected activities."},{"time":189866,"text":"Our idea was to bring all aspects\nof television-making"},{"time":193169,"text":"into one single structure: news,\nprogram production, broadcasting,"},{"time":197180,"text":"research and training, administration --"},{"time":199426,"text":"all into a circuit\nof interconnected activities"},{"time":203118,"text":"where people would meet in a process\nof exchange and collaboration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207959,"text":"I still very much like this image."},{"time":209801,"text":"It reminds one of biology classes,\nif you remember the human body"},{"time":212948,"text":"with all its organs\nand circulatory systems, like at school."},{"time":215876,"text":"And suddenly you think of architecture\nno longer as built substance,"},{"time":219897,"text":"but as an organism, as a life form."},{"time":222436,"text":"And as you start to dissect this organism,"},{"time":224807,"text":"you can identify a series\nof primary technical clusters --"},{"time":229560,"text":"program production,\nbroadcasting center and news."},{"time":232857,"text":"Those are tightly intertwined\nwith social clusters:"},{"time":236361,"text":"meeting rooms, canteens, chat areas --"},{"time":239449,"text":"informal spaces for people\nto meet and exchange."},{"time":243260,"text":"So the organizational structure\nof this building was a hybrid"},{"time":247522,"text":"between the technical and the social,"},{"time":249992,"text":"the human and the performative."},{"time":252333,"text":"And of course, we used the loop\nof the building as a circulatory system,"},{"time":255997,"text":"to thread everything together\nand to allow both visitors and staff"},{"time":259930,"text":"to experience all these different\nfunctions in a great unity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265118,"text":"With 473,000 square meters,"},{"time":268202,"text":"it is one of the largest buildings\never built in the world."},{"time":271237,"text":"It has a population of over 10,000 people,"},{"time":273929,"text":"and of course, this is a scale\nthat exceeds the comprehension"},{"time":277539,"text":"of many things and the scale\nof typical architecture."},{"time":280323,"text":"So we stopped work for a while"},{"time":281975,"text":"and sat down and cut 10,000 little sticks\nand glued them onto a model,"},{"time":286304,"text":"just simply to confront ourselves\nwith what that quantity actually meant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291261,"text":"But of course, it's not a number,"},{"time":292895,"text":"it is the people, it is a community\nthat inhabits the building,"},{"time":297528,"text":"and in order to both comprehend\nthis, but also script this architecture,"},{"time":302005,"text":"we identified five characters,\nhypothetical characters,"},{"time":305275,"text":"and we followed them throughout their day\nin a life in this building,"},{"time":309868,"text":"thought of where they would meet,\nwhat they would experience."},{"time":312775,"text":"So it was a way to script and design\nthe building, but of course,"},{"time":315938,"text":"also to communicate its experiences."},{"time":317999,"text":"This was part of an exhibition\nwith the Museum of Modern Art"},{"time":321311,"text":"in both New York and Beijing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324865,"text":"This is the main broadcast control room,"},{"time":327088,"text":"a technical installation so large,"},{"time":328930,"text":"it can broadcast over 200\nchannels simultaneously."},{"time":333643,"text":"And this is how the building\nstands in Beijing today."},{"time":337801,"text":"Its first broadcast live\nwas the London Olympics 2012,"},{"time":341119,"text":"after it had been completed\nfrom the outside for the Beijing Olympics."},{"time":345998,"text":"And you can see at the very tip\nof this 75-meter cantilever,"},{"time":350085,"text":"those three little circles."},{"time":351663,"text":"And they're indeed part of a public loop\nthat goes through the building."},{"time":355188,"text":"They're a piece of glass\nthat you can stand on"},{"time":357764,"text":"and watch the city pass by\nbelow you in slow motion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363524,"text":"The building has become\npart of everyday life in Beijing."},{"time":366798,"text":"It is there."},{"time":368313,"text":"It has also become a very popular backdrop"},{"time":371425,"text":"for wedding photography."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372934,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378621,"text":"But its most important moment\nis maybe sill this one."},{"time":381619,"text":"\"That's Beijing\" is similar to \"Time Out,\""},{"time":383697,"text":"a magazine that broadcasts what\nis happening in town during the week,"},{"time":388571,"text":"and suddenly you see the building\nportrayed no longer as physical matter,"},{"time":393558,"text":"but actually as an urban actor,"},{"time":395097,"text":"as part of a series of personas\nthat define the life of the city."},{"time":400987,"text":"So architecture suddenly\nassumes the quality of a player,"},{"time":405921,"text":"of something that writes stories\nand performs stories."},{"time":410619,"text":"And I think that could be one\nof its primary meanings"},{"time":414955,"text":"that we believe in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416226,"text":"But of course, there's another\nstory to this building."},{"time":418861,"text":"It is the story of the people\nthat made it --"},{"time":421814,"text":"400 engineers and architects\nthat I was guiding"},{"time":424656,"text":"over almost a decade of collaborative work"},{"time":427271,"text":"that we spent together\nin scripting this building,"},{"time":430262,"text":"in imagining its reality"},{"time":432192,"text":"and ultimately getting it built in China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437737,"text":"This is a residential development\nin Singapore, large scale."},{"time":442541,"text":"If we look at Singapore like most of Asia\nand more and more of the world,"},{"time":446795,"text":"of course, it is dominated by the tower,"},{"time":450366,"text":"a typology that indeed creates\nmore isolation than connectedness,"},{"time":454911,"text":"and I wanted to ask, how\ncould we think about living,"},{"time":458146,"text":"not only in terms of the privacy\nand individuality of ourselves"},{"time":461995,"text":"and our apartment,"},{"time":463455,"text":"but in an idea of a collective?"},{"time":466115,"text":"How could we think about creating\na communal environment"},{"time":469538,"text":"in which sharing things was as great\nas having your own?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":474664,"text":"The typical answer to the question --\nwe had to design 1,040 apartments --"},{"time":479384,"text":"would have looked like this:"},{"time":480765,"text":"24-story height limit given\nby the planning authorities,"},{"time":483535,"text":"12 towers with nothing\nbut residual in between --"},{"time":487533,"text":"a very tight system that,\nalthough the tower isolates you,"},{"time":490470,"text":"it doesn't even give you privacy,\nbecause you're so close to the next one,"},{"time":494001,"text":"that it is very questionable\nwhat the qualities of this would be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498488,"text":"So I proposed to topple the towers,\nthrow the vertical into the horizontal"},{"time":502806,"text":"and stack them up,"},{"time":504620,"text":"and what looks a bit random from the side,"},{"time":507191,"text":"if you look from the viewpoint\nof the helicopter,"},{"time":510009,"text":"you can see its organizational structure\nis actually a hexagonal grid,"},{"time":514762,"text":"in which these horizontal\nbuilding blocks are stacked up"},{"time":518523,"text":"to create huge outdoor courtyards --\ncentral spaces for the community,"},{"time":523616,"text":"programmed with a variety\nof amenities and functions."},{"time":527800,"text":"And you see that these courtyards\nare not hermetically sealed spaces."},{"time":531111,"text":"They're open, permeable;\nthey're interconnected."},{"time":533627,"text":"We called the project \"The Interlace,\""},{"time":535875,"text":"thinking that we interlace\nand interconnect"},{"time":538873,"text":"the human beings and the spaces alike."},{"time":542502,"text":"And the detailed quality\nof everything we designed"},{"time":545417,"text":"was about animating the space\nand giving the space to the inhabitants."},{"time":549273,"text":"And, in fact, it was a system"},{"time":550694,"text":"where we would layer\nprimarily communal spaces,"},{"time":554186,"text":"stacked to more and more\nindividual and private spaces."},{"time":558662,"text":"So we would open up a spectrum"},{"time":560529,"text":"between the collective and the individual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564203,"text":"A little piece of math:"},{"time":565378,"text":"if we count all the green\nthat we left on the ground,"},{"time":567953,"text":"minus the footprint of the buildings,"},{"time":570062,"text":"and we would add back\nthe green of all the terraces,"},{"time":573513,"text":"we have 112 percent green space,"},{"time":575591,"text":"so more nature than not\nhaving built a building."},{"time":578463,"text":"And of course this little piece of math\nshows you that we are multiplying"},{"time":582489,"text":"the space available\nto those who live there."},{"time":585830,"text":"This is, in fact, the 13th floor\nof one of these terraces."},{"time":589038,"text":"So you see new datum planes,\nnew grounds planes for social activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594792,"text":"We paid a lot of attention\nto sustainability."},{"time":598212,"text":"In the tropics, the sun is the most\nimportant thing to pay attention to,"},{"time":601815,"text":"and, in fact, it is seeking\nprotection from the sun."},{"time":604901,"text":"We first proved that all apartments\nwould have sufficient daylight"},{"time":608062,"text":"through the year."},{"time":609648,"text":"We then went on to optimize\nthe glazing of the facades"},{"time":612333,"text":"to minimize the energy\nconsumption of the building."},{"time":615981,"text":"But most importantly, we could prove\nthat through the geometry"},{"time":619420,"text":"of the building design,"},{"time":621020,"text":"the building itself would provide\nsufficient shading to the courtyards"},{"time":624406,"text":"so that those would be usable\nthroughout the entire year."},{"time":627432,"text":"We further placed water bodies\nalong the prevailing wind corridors,"},{"time":630934,"text":"so that evaporative cooling\nwould create microclimates"},{"time":634678,"text":"that, again, would enhance\nthe quality of those spaces"},{"time":638187,"text":"available for the inhabitants."},{"time":641773,"text":"And it was the idea of creating\nthis variety of choices,"},{"time":645543,"text":"of freedom to think\nwhere you would want to be,"},{"time":649640,"text":"where you would want to escape, maybe,"},{"time":651568,"text":"within the own complexity\nof the complex in which you live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657036,"text":"But coming from Asia to Europe:"},{"time":659100,"text":"a building for a German\nmedia company based in Berlin,"},{"time":662980,"text":"transitioning from the traditional\nprint media to the digital media."},{"time":667830,"text":"And its CEO asked a few\nvery pertinent questions:"},{"time":671146,"text":"Why would anyone today\nstill want to go to the office,"},{"time":673775,"text":"because you can actually work anywhere?"},{"time":675988,"text":"And how could a digital identity\nof a company be embodied"},{"time":679885,"text":"in a building?"},{"time":682147,"text":"We created not only an object,\nbut at the center of this object"},{"time":685994,"text":"we created a giant space,"},{"time":687613,"text":"and this space was about\nthe experience of a collective,"},{"time":691311,"text":"the experience of collaboration\nand of togetherness."},{"time":695011,"text":"Communication, interaction\nas the center of a space"},{"time":698650,"text":"that in itself would float,"},{"time":701213,"text":"like what we call the collaborative cloud,"},{"time":703349,"text":"in the middle of the building,"},{"time":704881,"text":"surrounded by an envelope\nof standard modular offices."},{"time":708944,"text":"So with only a few steps\nfrom your quiet work desk,"},{"time":712118,"text":"you could participate\nin the giant collective experience"},{"time":715869,"text":"of the central space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720159,"text":"Finally, we come to London,\na project commissioned"},{"time":723762,"text":"by the London Legacy\nDevelopment Corporation"},{"time":726364,"text":"of the Mayor of London."},{"time":728309,"text":"We were asked to undertake a study"},{"time":730521,"text":"and investigate the potential of a site"},{"time":733337,"text":"out in Stratford in the Olympic Park."},{"time":736229,"text":"In the 19th century, Prince Albert\nhad created Albertopolis."},{"time":740513,"text":"And Boris Johnson thought\nof creating Olympicopolis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745211,"text":"The idea was to bring together\nsome of Britain's greatest institutions,"},{"time":749507,"text":"some international ones,\nand to create a new system of synergies."},{"time":753803,"text":"Prince Albert, as yet, created\nAlbertopolis in the 19th century,"},{"time":758351,"text":"thought of showcasing\nall achievements of mankind,"},{"time":760838,"text":"bringing arts and science closer together."},{"time":764082,"text":"And he built Exhibition Road,\na linear sequence of those institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769836,"text":"But of course, today's society\nhas moved on from there."},{"time":773551,"text":"We no longer live in a world"},{"time":775531,"text":"in which everything\nis as clearly delineated"},{"time":778235,"text":"or separated from each other."},{"time":779761,"text":"We live in a world in which\nboundaries start to blur"},{"time":783174,"text":"between the different domains,"},{"time":784666,"text":"and in which collaboration and interaction\nbecomes far more important"},{"time":788680,"text":"than keeping separations."},{"time":791408,"text":"So we wanted to think\nof a giant culture machine,"},{"time":794451,"text":"a building that would orchestrate\nand animate the various domains,"},{"time":799252,"text":"but allow them to interact\nand collaborate."},{"time":803211,"text":"At the base of it is a very simple module,"},{"time":805340,"text":"a ring module."},{"time":806515,"text":"It can function as a double-loaded\ncorridor, has daylight, has ventilation."},{"time":810182,"text":"It can be glazed over"},{"time":811357,"text":"and turned into a giant\nexhibitional performance space."},{"time":814254,"text":"These modules were stacked together"},{"time":816403,"text":"with the idea that almost any\nfunction could, over time,"},{"time":820189,"text":"occupy any of these modules."},{"time":821950,"text":"So institutions could shrink or contract,"},{"time":825090,"text":"as, of course, the future of culture\nis, in a way, the most uncertain of all."},{"time":830733,"text":"This is how the building sits,\nadjacent to the Aquatics Centre,"},{"time":833712,"text":"opposite the Olympic Stadium."},{"time":836608,"text":"And you can see how\nits cantilevering volumes"},{"time":838965,"text":"project out and engage the public space"},{"time":841779,"text":"and how its courtyards\nanimate the public inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847313,"text":"The idea was to create a complex system"},{"time":850565,"text":"in which institutional entities\ncould maintain their own identity,"},{"time":855477,"text":"in which they would not\nbe subsumed in a singular volume."},{"time":858434,"text":"Here's a scale comparison\nto the Centre Pompidou in Paris."},{"time":861624,"text":"It both shows the enormous scale\nand potential of the project,"},{"time":865013,"text":"but also the difference:"},{"time":866324,"text":"here, it is a multiplicity\nof a heterogeneous structure,"},{"time":870523,"text":"in which different entities can interact"},{"time":873058,"text":"without losing their own identity."},{"time":876395,"text":"And it was this thought: to create\nan organizational structure"},{"time":880369,"text":"that would allow for multiple\nnarratives to be scripted --"},{"time":883226,"text":"for those in the educational parts\nthat create and think culture;"},{"time":888704,"text":"for those that present\nthe visual arts, the dance;"},{"time":892234,"text":"and for the public to be\nadmitted into all of this"},{"time":895067,"text":"with a series of possible trajectories,"},{"time":897737,"text":"to script their own reading\nof these narratives"},{"time":900493,"text":"and their own experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904475,"text":"And I want to end on a project\nthat is very small,"},{"time":907905,"text":"in a way, very different:"},{"time":909896,"text":"a floating cinema\nin the ocean of Thailand."},{"time":911968,"text":"Friends of mine had founded\na film festival,"},{"time":915528,"text":"and I thought,"},{"time":917226,"text":"if we think of the stories\nand narratives of movies,"},{"time":920529,"text":"we should also think of the narratives\nof the people that watch them."},{"time":924096,"text":"So I designed a small\nmodular floating platform,"},{"time":927405,"text":"based on the techniques\nof local fishermen,"},{"time":929703,"text":"how they built their lobster\nand fish farms."},{"time":931814,"text":"We collaborated with the local community"},{"time":934217,"text":"and built, out of recycled\nmaterials of their own,"},{"time":937973,"text":"this fantastical floating platform"},{"time":940119,"text":"that gently moved in the ocean"},{"time":942064,"text":"as we watched films\nfrom the British film archive,"},{"time":944972,"text":"[1903] \"Alice in Wonderland,\" for example."},{"time":947987,"text":"The most primordial\nexperiences of the audience"},{"time":951068,"text":"merged with the stories of the movies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955840,"text":"So I believe that architecture exceeds\nthe domain of physical matter,"},{"time":960674,"text":"of the built environment,"},{"time":962158,"text":"but is really about how\nwe want to live our lives,"},{"time":965371,"text":"how we script our own stories\nand those of others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968885,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970060,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}